body:
You’ll forget tomorrow

Harry styles imagines where he showed up drunk at y/n’s porch.

My phone rings for thousand times tonight. I rolled over my bed used at whoever is calling me nonstop at three in the morning.

Grabbing my phone , checking the id I was surprised when I saw it’s Harry. Harry styles. My best friend that ditch me because of his new girlfriend. Who I have more feelings toward him that a friend.

I answered not sure why he’s calling me “Harry?” I asked worried. Is he good or maybe he had broke up with his girlfriend and now is looking for a friend.

“Oh y/nnnnnn” his voice is strange and I know for sure he’s more than drunk. I hesitate, don’t know how to control this situation “are you ok?” He laughed “no no I’m Harry,y/n” I sigh , changing my position on bed.

“Where are you now?” He for sure needs help if he’s this drunk “at your porch”.

He’s in front of my house at this time of the night? I hanged up and grab a hoodie nearby to wear on my single t-shirt.

Opening the door I saw him lays on my mat “oh god harry” I kneeled to help him stand up. His body is burning and he looks pale.

Sweat is running down his face.

“Y/n , my sweet y/n” he hold my face as I helped him up “I missed you” he whispered almost falling on me.

He’s heavier than me but we finally get in my room “don’t leave me, I don’t feel good” he grabs my hand when I wanted to bring him some coffee. His world touched my heart. I just can’t ignore him and his eyes.

“I’m not going anywhere, ok?” He nods but still holding my hand. I sigh and start to taking off his boots.

“I don’t feel good” he said again , I’m not sure if he meant throwing up or in general so I grabbed a nearest bin to put near him in case he throw up.

“Let’s just sleep on your side, ok?” I helped him to roll on his side. He shakes his head “no no, I want to sleep near you” I rolled my eyes at his cheekiness “ok then” I sit beside him and leaned on my bed post.

He rolled on his side as he puts his head on my chest and grabs my waist, a soft sigh left his mouth as he closed his eyes

“I love you y/n” he said and shocked me. Never in our friendship we said such a thing to each other, the line had more meaning for me at least but now I’m not sure why he’s telling me this.

“I love you , don’t leave me again” he said holding me tighter. I played with his hair , enjoying the moment , even if he will forget tomorrow I should tell him at least once “I love you harry” and I I meant it.

body:
Harry Styles’ Auftritt bei der Met Gala löst Diskussionen um seine Sexualität aus

What an awful article. German gossip websites annoy me.

- His fans were not surprised, they even expected him to be more extravagant, but he was on theme and enjoyed expressing himself.

- Why do they still need to call him Taylor’s Ex, that “relationship” was years ago and really short.

- He expressed his feminine site quite often in the past years.

- There is no need to label his sexuality, ha said he does not need labels, so please respect that.

- Please research the MET-gala, when you have to write an article about it.

summary: How Harry Styles Conquered The Met Gala 2019
title: How Harry Styles Conquered The Met Gala 2019
description:
Harry Styles has come a long, long way. From the wide-eyed, spritely innocence of an X Factor bronze medal to performing on-stage with Stevie Nicks, the 25-year-old is now a style icon proper. Better yet, he not only co-chaired the Met Gala 2019 (an impressive gig shared by the likes of Lady Gaga and Serena Williams), but he conquered the night outright.

How? Well, what is a notoriously abstract theme - the ‘Notes On Camp’ dress code is based upon a seminal Susan Sontag essay on the performative, unexpected, serious-bashing sentiment that defines camp culture - found a happy home on Styles’ shoulders.

He looked to the theatre of a Georgian marquis drunk on red wine and ruffles. He combined typical masculine and feminine traits with a tailored silhouette and translucent fabric and a pearl earring all from Gucci. He managed to make camp his own thing, looking relaxed in the process. No mean feat, especially amongst a crowd that’s arguably more well-versed in the art of Big Industry Events.

Styles, in short, did his homework. There’s a look that ticks off the dress code, but it’s one that makes a wider statement: that guys increasingly don’t have to stick to norms, and that we can have fun at the same time. Of course, what works at the Met Gala is a long way away from real life. That’s the whole point. But look beyond the gilded parties of Anna Wintour, and it’s another welcome sign of menswear loosening things up and letting self-expression run amok.

You’re a wizard, Harry.
